observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require:

a.	The Municipal Accountant to furnish the Audit Team with subsidiary schedules of PPE and schedule of depreciation charges to facilitate the verification of the computation of the depreciation expenses of all depreciable assets;

b.	The Municipal Accountant and GSO-designate to investigate and reconcile immediately the discrepancies between the PPE balances per accounting records and RPCPPE of the Inventory Committee; 

c.	Municipal Accountant, Municipal Treasurer and Inventory Committee to undertake collaborative procedure to ensure that all PPEs included in the RPCPPE are duly recorded in their respective records; and,

d.	The Municipal Accountant and the GSO-Designate to maintain and update the PPE Ledger Cards (PPELC) and Property Cards, respectively, and regularly reconcile with the General Ledger and Inventory Report to come up with the reconciled balances of PPE accounts to be considered as the correct balance of the LGU’s PPEs.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive require the Municipal Accountant to:

To trace the misstatement from prior years; 

Make adjusting entry to reflect the correct balance of the affected accounts to reconcile the book and bank balances.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive direct the Municipal Accountant to:
Prepare the necessary accounting journal entries to record the reconciling items totaling P6,110,553.74;
Cause the reconciliation of the total amounts of CiB-LCCA between the subsidiary ledgers and that presented in the SFPos under the Trust Fund;
Obtain copies of Bank Statements to facilitate the preparation of BRS for DBP Bank Account Nos. CA-0725-034159-080 and 0-1445-725-9, and LBP Account No. 1192-1230-93; and
Take up the necessary accounting journal entry to close the non-existent bank account with a book balance of P36,287.65.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive require:
The Inventory Committee to conduct the annual physical inventory of its PPEs, prepare the RPCPPE and furnish copy thereof to the Audit Team;
The GSO and Municipal Accountant to maintain and update the PPE Cards and PPE Ledger Cards, respectively, and provide a copy thereof to the Audit Team;
The Municipal Accountant to provide the allowance for depreciation on all depreciable items of PPE, with supporting computation thereof in a lapsing schedule, and furnish the Audit Team.

We recommended for the Municipal Mayor to direct the Municipal Accountant - In Charge the following:

To use the correct accounts in the recording of PPE prescribed by COA Circular No. 2015-009 dated December 1, 2015;

To prepare adjusting entries to reclassify the completed projects to appropriate PPE accounts from the Construction in Progress accounts;

To reclassify the PPE accounts which were incorrectly recorded; and

To furnish the audit team the JEVs to record the adjusting entries for purposes of verification.

We recommended to the Municipal Mayor the following courses of action:

Direct the Municipal Planning and Development Coordinator to strictly monitor and carefully evaluate the implementation of the PPAs for which the fund transfers were intended for;

Direct the Municipal Engineer to administer, supervise and control the implementation of the PPAs related to engineering and public works and establish close coordination with the Municipal Planning and Development Coordinator;

Direct the concerned Department Heads to have close coordination with Municipal Planning and Development Coordinator and Municipal Engineer regarding to the PPAs related to their respective offices;

Direct the Municipal Accountant to explain the non-liquidation of fully utilized fund transfers and to liquidate accordingly those fund transfers whose PPAs were already completed; and

Direct the Municipal Treasurer to determine the availability of cash of all fund transfers which are reported in the books and issue the check in favor of the Source Agencies to return all unused amount. In case the source agency could no longer be identified, the check shall be made in favor of the Bureau of Treasury.

We recommend to compel the General Services Officer and Municipal Accountant to:
Prepare and submit all documents and reports such as duly approved RIS to evidence the issuance of the materials from stock and Report of Supplies and Materials Issued etc. as basis for crediting the non-existing balance from the books;
Direct the General Services Officer or the Municipal Treasurer to prepare the Summary of Supplies and Materials Issued (SSMI) weekly as a basis by the Accounting Unit in preparing the JEV to record the supplies and materials issued;
Adjust the non-existing and consumed unaccounted materials inventory in the books.

We recommend that the Municipal Accountant:
Comply with the provisions of Sections 43 of the Manual of the NGAS, Volume I on the proper recording of purchases and issuances of supplies and materials;
Restore to inventory accounts the undocumented P2,156,888.60 adjustments; and
Maintain the Subsidiary Ledger Card (SLC) for inventories.

We recommend that the Municipal Mayor:
Require the General Services Office or the Municipal Treasurer to conduct inventory taking periodically and submit the inventory report for periodic reconciliation of records between the General Services and Accounting Unit;
Require the General Services Officer or the Municipal Treasurer and Municipal Account to maintain and update regularly the SCs and SLCs for each inventory item, regularly reconcile their records and immediately effect the necessary adjustments in the books of accounts and/or supply records for any differences noted;
Submit the SSMI and RIS as supporting document to the issuances of inventory as drawn in the general journal;
Require the Accounting Office and the signing official in the purchase order, to supply needed information in the disbursement vouchers and purchase orders; and
Classify and record transactions to appropriate accounts.

We recommend that the Municipal Mayor direct the Municipal Engineer/BAC Chairman to ensure that:
A list of the Municipality’s programs/projects and activities, inclusive of those for implementation and non-infrastructure projects is submitted to the Audit Team at the beginning of the year;
Relevant information regarding the PPAs of the Municipality be posted in  signboards or black/bulletin boards  following the provisions of the cited Circular;
The Audit Team be informed that the appropriate project signboards and/or notices have been  posted  within ten (10) days after the award of the infrastructure project or before the start of the program/activity; and
Maintain updated Project Status based on the data sourced from the monthly monitoring report prepared by Municipality.
